      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AFTER THE CHASE (6) was ultra-impressive at his latest appearance at Port Pirie, scoring comfortably by 16 metres after taking control of the race a fair way from home. That made it three wins on the trot. Draws wider but came from a deeper barrier to win here earlier in the month. Can deliver again. NEDS BEACH NZ (1) came from the back row when second to AFTER THE CHASE last week. Has ground to make up on that rival but does get the aid of the ace draw. JAWSOFGOODTIME (8) was out of the money as favourite last time but had recorded two wins and a placing from the previous three outings so is worth another chance. GOLDEN JAYLET (2) draws well again and is worth including off a last-start win by close to 11 metres at this venue.",
